SIMPLE: stringy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stringy
<hw>String"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Consisting of strings, or small threads; fibrous; filamentous;
<as>as, a <ex>stringy</ex> root</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of being drawn into a string, as a glutinous
substance; ropy; viscid; gluely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stringy bark</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a name
given in Australia to several trees of the genus <gen>Eucalyptus</gen>
(as <spn>Eucalyptus amygdalina</spn>, <spn>Eucalyptus obliqua</spn>,
<spn>Eucalyptus capitellata</spn>, <spn>Eucalyptus macrorhyncha</spn>,
<spn>Eucalyptus piperita</spn>, <spn>Eucalyptus pilularis</spn>, ⟦and⟧
<spn>Eucalyptus tetradonta</spn>), which have a fibrous bark used by the
aborigines for making cordage and cloth.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strip</ent>⟦br⟧
